nfiguration should remain compatible, so I can proceed with the upgrade steps. I'm setting up the migration path: first upgrading from 3.9 to 3.13 and rolling out the change, then enabling all feature flags on that version, updating the configmap to replace the deprecated queue_master_locator setting with the 4.x equivalent, and finally upgrading to 4.1.\n\nI need to be careful about the rolling upgrade mechanics here—within the same major version, nodes can temporarily run different patch versions, but for a major version jump to 4.x, all nodes need to be on 3.13 first before proceeding. The StatefulSet's rolling update strategy will upgrade from the highest index downward, so I'll have a mixed-version cluster during the transition that I need to monitor closely.\n\nThe startup probe command `rabbitmq-diagnostics check_running` should remain compatible across all these versions, so that's not a blocker. I'll proceed with the upgrade and let the rolling update strategy handle the sequential pod updates.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3494,"cache_read_input_tokens":32580,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3494},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74643e4c-336b-4456-86ab-ce7c25c206bf","uuid":"ddd7852e-a1f4-4b50-80cc-0bfe51a521da","request_id":"req_011CcMtU6BmtEcJy33RVdamm"}
