{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CLjZjrDNgrmFqqLZGXWXeq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is clear: \n\n```\nFeature flags: `classic_mirrored_queue_version`: required feature flag not enabled! It must be enabled before upgrading RabbitMQ.\n```\n\nThis means the `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag must be enabled on the 3.9 nodes BEFORE upgrading to 3.13. \n\nThe issue is: rabbitmq-2 got upgraded to 3.13, but the existing data (from 3.9) doesn't have the required feature flags enabled.\n\nI need to:\n1. Roll back rabbitmq-2 to 3.9 first (or let it fail and fix from the still-running 3.9 nodes)\n2. Enable the feature flags on the running 3.9 nodes, then proceed with the upgrade\n\nSince I can't easily roll back the StatefulSet image change, I'll use a partition to halt the rolling update. I can set the partition to prevent further updates while I enable the feature flags on rabbitmq-0 and rabbitmq-1, then resume the upgrade process.\n\nBut here's the real problem: rabbitmq-2's PVC still contains the old 3.9 data where the `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag isn't enabled. When 3.13 starts up and reads the Mnesia database from disk, it checks whether the required feature flags are present.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider how RabbitMQ stores feature flags—each node maintains its own copy in Mnesia, so when rabbitmq-2 was upgraded to 3.13, its local Mnesia data doesn't have the flag enabled yet.  When it restarts, it reads from its own PVC which still has the old state, so enabling the flag on the 3.9 nodes won't automatically propagate to rabbitmq-2's isolated Mnesia copy.\n\nI'm weighing two approaches: either enable the feature flags on the running nodes first and then manually clear rabbitmq-2's Mnesia data so it syncs fresh from the cluster, or consider rolling back the upgrade entirely. The challenge is that we need the flag enabled before 3.13 can start, but we also can't lose the PVC data.\n\nFor the rollback approach, I'd patch the StatefulSet back to 3.9, wait for rabbitmq-2 to rejoin as 3.9, enable all feature flags across the cluster, then upgrade to 3.13 again. But I'm realizing that changing the image back to 3.9 will trigger another rolling update in reverse, which could complicate things further. I need to figure out which feature flags are actually required in 3.13 and whether they exist in 3.9, since I can only enable flags that are available in the current version. Let me simplify this: roll back to 3.9, enable the necessary feature flags there, then upgrade everything to 3.13 at once.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1553,"cache_read_input_tokens":39626,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1553},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74643e4c-336b-4456-86ab-ce7c25c206bf","uuid":"54bbbddf-e57c-474f-b2a8-4705748e40b9","request_id":"req_011CcMuHua8rjpbjBGEdVf4r"}
